## Database Migrations

The application includes a **migration administration interface** accessible at `/admin/migrations`. It allows you to manage database migrations without using the command line.

**Available operations:**

- **Run migrations**: runs all pending migrations (`php artisan migrate`)
- **Rollback**: rolls back the last batch of migrations (`php artisan migrate:rollback`), with an optional step parameter to roll back multiple batches
- **Fresh migration**: drops all tables and re-runs all migrations (`php artisan migrate:fresh`) — **all data will be lost**
- **Migration status**: shows the status of all migrations, loaded automatically on page open and refreshable on demand

Migrate and migrate:fresh run as **asynchronous background jobs** — the page polls for completion and shows the output when done. Rollback runs synchronously and returns the output immediately.

> ⚠️ **Warning**: `migrate:fresh` is a destructive operation. All data in the database will be permanently deleted.

**Access control:**

By default, **only `superadmin` role** can access the migration administration. To grant access to other roles, add policies to the `ac_rules` table:

```csv
p,admin,Migrations,read
p,admin,Migrations,create
```

## Database Seeding Administration

The application includes a **seeding administration interface** accessible at `/admin/seeder`. It allows you to run seeders without using the command line, individually or in bulk.

